args:
The Orichalcum Chef is a grand contest to find
the world's greatest culinary artist. But when
the venue for this festival of flavor is attacked
by a hungry dragon, the prince and his friends
offer to hold it at the castle. Now it's out of the
frying pan and into the fire for everyone!
Epicureans, foodies, and devotees of\nflavor alike...the moment you've all\nbeen waiting for is here at last!

Your taste buds will trill with delight as our
culinary warriors throw down their oven
mitts in a contest to find out who is the
greatest. This is...Orichalcum Chef!

Our competition sees first-rate culinary
artisans from lands near and far come to
the most sacred of gourmet battlegrounds:
THE HUUUUUNGERDOOOOOME!
(I swear on my honor as a Nanakusa\nthat I'm NOT going to lose today.)
(I've gathered top-shelf ingredients,\nand it's time to prove I'm worthy of\nbeing called the world's greatest chef.)
(I must see my dreams made reality...\nAnd to do that, I must be the champion!)

What manner of mouth-watering meals
will our chefs create, and who among
them will return home with the honor
of being crowned a culinary master?!
Hot damn, I thought that guy would never\nshut up. The only kinda gum-flappin' I like\nis the one where I'm eatin' a turkey leg!
Yes, but we sure had an eventful couple\nof days leading up to this, didn't we?
Nimis HUNGRY! Nimis need to EAT!
Nooo, stop! Stop eating all the food!\nYou're making an absolute disaster\nof the storehouse!
That giant thing can't actually\nbe a DRAGON, right?!
Hang on. I came here for a cooking\ncontest, not to watch some big fat\ndragon get bigger and fatter!
Well, we need to stop it before we don't\nhave two graham crackers left to rub\ntogether. C'mon, everyone!

NOOOOO! IT'S GONNA EAT HIM!
*sigh* Good night, sweet prince.
I'll make sure there are always
pretty flowers on your grave.
I talk Nimis indeed. You do realize that\nyou are gobbling up all the ingredients\nfor the cooking contest, yes?
Now then, if you could be so kind as to put\nthat gentleman down and behave yourself,\nI will prepare you a much tastier treat.
Whew! Thought I was a goner there.\nThank you very much, er...
Buddy, you better be some kind of crazy\nSUPER chef if you're planning to whip up\na treat that satisfies Ol' Gutbomb here!
Allay your fears, good faerie. For I wear \nthe mantle of chef precisely that I might\ncreate tongue-dazzling meals for guests!
These scattered vegetables will make the\nbasis of a fine meal. Then a bit of this...
I can't believe you stopped a rampaging\ndragon with the power of COOKING!
We owe more than we can say, Valerio.\nOh, I'm Prince {player_name},\nand these are my friends.
Are you here to compete in the cooking\ncompetition that's happening soon?
Indeed. And as you do not appear to be\nchefs yourselves, might I assume you\nare patrons of the gastronomic arts?

I ain't sure what that word means, but I'll
tell ya who's got two thumbs, a grumbly
belly, and wants to watch some cookin'!
THIS GUY! ...Oh, and my pals, yeah?
But how will they ever hold such a\ncompetition when that dragon ate\na full half of the ingredients?
Leave it to ol' Ranzal, 'cause I gots me\na plan. What say we have 'em sling hash\nback at the Halidom instead?!
That's a fine idea, Ranzal; the nearby\nwoods should provide us with more\nthan enough ingredients.
Oh man, I can't wait what to get all them\nfancy chefs under our roof...and then eat\nEVERYTHING THEY MAKE!
While we are grateful for your proposal,\nthe Orichalcum Chef competition has a\nlong and storied history.
Our contest has always been held within\nthe hallowed halls of the Hungerdome,\nand there it must remain.
Oh, come on! We got a freakin' CASTLE!
Perhaps there is yet a way\nfor us to make this work.
I do indeed. Do you see this stadium?

If you can uproot it from its current spot
and carry it to the castle, I will personally
see to it that you receive a banquet fit for
dragon royalty. What say you?
Well, there can be no eating without\nhonest work, so if you would be so kind?
Holy refried beans! He yanked the\nwhole stadium right outta the ground!
Could he really be intending to carry it\nall the way to the Halidom?
Are you kiddin' me? I'D carry the damn\nstadium if it meant I got to chow down.\nNow hurry up and follow that dragon!
...What an unexpected series of events.\nStill, I'm glad things seem to be going\noff without a hitch now.
I can't WAIT to see all this chow, and I\ncan't wait even MORE what to eat it!\n...Oh, and see who wins, I guess.

And now, our gastronomic virtuosos will
let fly spatulas and sous-vide steaks in the
battle to be named the Orichalcum Chef.
Good luck to all, and...ALLEZ CUISINE!
